1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the performance impact of LoS and NLoS transmissions in small cell networks, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the area spectral efficiency (ASE) of small cell networks, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of LoS and NLoS transmissions on the coverage probability and ASE, which are important metrics for multimedia applications. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper studies the performance of small cell networks, which can be viewed as a complex system, and proposes a path loss model to analyze its behavior. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - The paper does not directly relate to this sub-category, but it is possible that the results of this study could have implications for the societal impact of small cell networks.
